<i>noun</i>: 훈수 [훈ː수], 충언 [충언], 충고 [충고], 참모 [참모], 조언 [조ː언], 일침 [일침], 도움말 [도움말], 경종 [경ː종], 간언 [가ː넌] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>훈수 [훈ː수]</dt><br>
<dd>1. kibitzing; help; tip</dd><br>
<dd>바둑이나 장기 등을 둘 때 구경하던 사람이 끼어들어 수를 가르쳐 줌.</dd><br>
<dd>In playing go or janggi, Korean chess, etc., a state in which a non-participant intervenes and teaches a player what to do with a move.</dd><br>
<dd>2. advice; tip; hint</dd><br>
<dd>남의 일에 끼어들어 이래라저래라 참견하는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>Words uttered when one intervenes in another's affairs and tells him/her what to do.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>충언 [충언]</dt><br>
<dd>1. advice</dd><br>
<dd>남이 잘못을 고치도록 진심으로 타이르는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>Sincere words given to someone to correct his/her fault or mistake.</dd><br>
<dd>2. honest talk</dd><br>
<dd>마음속에서 우러나오는 충성스럽고 정직한 말.</dd><br>
<dd>Loyal and honest words, which one feels deep in one's heart.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>충고 [충고]</dt><br>
<dd>advice</dd><br>
<dd>남의 허물이나 잘못을 진심으로 타이름. 또는 그런 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of talking sincerely to someone to correct his/her fault or mistake, or such a remark.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>참모 [참모]</dt><br>
<dd>1. advice; adviser; aid</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람의 곁에서 의견을 내어 도움. 또는 그런 사람.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of assisting one's superior by giving him/her advice, or a person with such a duty.</dd><br>
<dd>2. staff officer</dd><br>
<dd>군대에서 지휘관을 돕는 업무를 맡은 장교.</dd><br>
<dd>A military officer who assists a commander.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>조언 [조ː언]</dt><br>
<dd>advice</dd><br>
<dd>도움이 되도록 말로 거들거나 깨우쳐 줌. 또는 그런 말.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of helping another by offering counsel or enlightening him/her, or such counsel.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>일침 [일침]</dt><br>
<dd>advice; warning</dd><br>
<dd>따끔할 정도로 정확하고 날카로운 충고나 경고.</dd><br>
<dd>A poignant and accurate piece of advice.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>도움말 [도움말]</dt><br>
<dd>advice; tips; help</dd><br>
<dd>도움이 되도록 일러주는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>Recommendations to help someone make an informed decision.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>경종 [경ː종]</dt><br>
<dd>1. signal; alarm</dd><br>
<dd>위급한 상황이나 위험 등을 알리는 종이나 사이렌 등의 신호.</dd><br>
<dd>A signal such as a bell sound or siren, informing many people of an emergency or danger.</dd><br>
<dd>2. warning; advice</dd><br>
<dd>잘못된 일이나 위험한 일에 대한 경계나 충고.</dd><br>
<dd>A warning or advice about something wrong or a danger.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>간언 [가ː넌]</dt><br>
<dd>expostulation; remonstrance; advice</dd><br>
<dd>웃어른이나 임금에게 잘못을 고치도록 하는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A piece of advice one gives to one's senior or a king, to correct something unjust or erroneous he/she has done.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>